1
00:01:26,900 --> 00:01:35,030
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,420 --> 00:01:37,729
[Episode 11]

3
00:01:40,180 --> 00:01:40,910
Shen Ranran,

4
00:01:41,150 --> 00:01:42,009
you have a call!

5
00:01:42,900 --> 00:01:45,830
-Maybe calling about when I join the crew.
-Go ahead.

6
00:01:50,450 --> 00:01:50,850
Hello?

7
00:01:52,590 --> 00:01:53,590
Mr. Cui, go ahead.

8
00:01:54,700 --> 00:01:55,229
Ranran,

9
00:01:55,950 --> 00:01:57,550
I have something to tell you.

10
00:01:58,000 --> 00:01:59,310
I'm at your beck and call.

11
00:01:59,310 --> 00:02:00,570
Whatever you say goes.

12
00:02:02,780 --> 00:02:03,180
Hello?

13
00:02:05,510 --> 00:02:05,930
Hello?

14
00:02:07,340 --> 00:02:07,800
Ranran,

15
00:02:08,340 --> 00:02:09,340
here's the thing.

16
00:02:10,210 --> 00:02:13,210
You know how unpredictable
the weather can be, right?

17
00:02:13,870 --> 00:02:14,930
Is it going to rain?

18
00:02:16,870 --> 00:02:17,640
No.

19
00:02:19,680 --> 00:02:21,079
I don't see any rain here.

20
00:02:21,650 --> 00:02:23,579
I don't even know what to say to you.

21
00:02:24,030 --> 00:02:25,940
I mean, some things

22
00:02:26,020 --> 00:02:28,280
don't always turn out the way you expect.

23
00:02:28,310 --> 00:02:29,640
There could be changes.

24
00:02:30,690 --> 00:02:33,090
I'm not getting
the third female lead role?

25
00:02:34,750 --> 00:02:35,380
It's okay.

26
00:02:36,130 --> 00:02:37,650
Fourth, fifth, or sixth lead,

27
00:02:37,650 --> 00:02:40,370
featured extra, or even just an extra—
I can do it.

28
00:02:40,370 --> 00:02:40,829
Ranran,

29
00:02:41,130 --> 00:02:42,260
don't get worked up.

30
00:02:43,060 --> 00:02:44,790
I'll just be straight with you.

31
00:02:44,970 --> 00:02:46,690
Your role as the third female lead

32
00:02:46,690 --> 00:02:48,420
has been given to someone else.

33
00:02:51,620 --> 00:02:54,400
I... got replaced?

34
00:02:54,590 --> 00:02:55,180
Yes.

35
00:02:55,270 --> 00:02:57,400
All the other roles have been cast too.

36
00:02:58,340 --> 00:02:59,740
You can't be in this show.

37
00:03:01,340 --> 00:03:03,280
Ranran? Ranran?

38
00:03:10,560 --> 00:03:11,310
Mr. Cui.

39
00:03:11,710 --> 00:03:12,710
Mr. Cui, please talk to the director.

40
00:03:12,710 --> 00:03:13,520
I will do my best

41
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:14,120
in this role.

42
00:03:14,120 --> 00:03:14,780
It's not about

43
00:03:14,780 --> 00:03:16,710
whether you can play the part well.

44
00:03:16,960 --> 00:03:17,500
But...

45
00:03:17,780 --> 00:03:18,750
they'd already decided that role was mine.

46
00:03:18,750 --> 00:03:19,860
How can they just replace me?

47
00:03:19,860 --> 00:03:20,530
How would I know?

48
00:03:20,530 --> 00:03:23,130
Someone came out of nowhere
and took your role!

49
00:03:23,150 --> 00:03:24,610
I want to see the director.

50
00:03:26,840 --> 00:03:28,430
Why go see the director?

51
00:03:28,910 --> 00:03:30,910
You'd only put him in an awkward spot.

52
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:31,890
No matter what,

53
00:03:32,340 --> 00:03:34,000
I have to talk to the director.

54
00:03:34,130 --> 00:03:35,860
I need to show him my sincerity.

55
00:03:36,460 --> 00:03:37,530
If the director could make the call,

56
00:03:37,530 --> 00:03:39,460
he would've kept you, wouldn't he?

57
00:03:41,810 --> 00:03:43,150
Then what should I do now?

58
00:03:43,150 --> 00:03:44,079
How would I know?

59
00:03:47,300 --> 00:03:49,360
This kind of thing happens every day.

60
00:03:50,030 --> 00:03:51,030
In this industry,

61
00:03:51,340 --> 00:03:52,600
without connections,

62
00:03:52,750 --> 00:03:54,300
you really won't get anywhere.

63
00:03:54,300 --> 00:03:56,630
But I didn't have any connections before,

64
00:03:57,250 --> 00:03:58,470
and I still got the role.

65
00:03:58,470 --> 00:03:59,329
Did you really?

66
00:03:59,840 --> 00:04:01,030
You just got replaced, didn't you?

67
00:04:01,030 --> 00:04:01,690
Didn't you?

68
00:04:05,180 --> 00:04:06,190
Don't... Don't...

69
00:04:06,190 --> 00:04:07,250
Don't... don't...

70
00:04:07,300 --> 00:04:09,000
Don't cry. Don't cry. Alright.

71
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:09,460
Well...

72
00:04:12,340 --> 00:04:13,200
How about this?

73
00:04:13,680 --> 00:04:14,880
The biggest investor

74
00:04:15,150 --> 00:04:16,010
in this show

75
00:04:16,010 --> 00:04:16,829
is Mr. Chu.

76
00:04:17,769 --> 00:04:18,430
I'm actually

77
00:04:18,430 --> 00:04:19,829
on decent enough terms with him.

78
00:04:19,829 --> 00:04:21,370
He's somebody in the industry too.

79
00:04:21,370 --> 00:04:22,570
I'll see if I can

80
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:23,690
introduce you to each other.

81
00:04:23,690 --> 00:04:24,820
If this works out...

82
00:04:25,430 --> 00:04:26,560
it's your last shot.

83
00:04:29,040 --> 00:04:29,620
Okay?

84
00:04:31,450 --> 00:04:34,400
[Seasons Change Hostel]

85
00:04:33,130 --> 00:04:34,659
Is that investor reliable?

86
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:36,790
I don't know.

87
00:04:37,770 --> 00:04:39,500
What's that investor's name?

88
00:04:41,920 --> 00:04:44,300
His name is... Chu Caiyuan.

89
00:04:47,830 --> 00:04:48,240
Okay.

90
00:04:48,810 --> 00:04:49,570
Later,

91
00:04:49,690 --> 00:04:51,800
I'll ask around
with the assistant directors I know

92
00:04:51,800 --> 00:04:52,870
about this guy.

93
00:04:54,070 --> 00:04:54,570
Right.

94
00:04:55,270 --> 00:04:56,770
I can also ask around the crew

95
00:04:56,770 --> 00:04:58,310
to see what that investor is like too.

96
00:04:58,310 --> 00:04:58,690
Okay.

97
00:04:59,180 --> 00:05:01,130
Beijing is huge.
There are all sorts of people here.

98
00:05:01,130 --> 00:05:03,410
It doesn't matter what kind of man he is!

99
00:05:03,920 --> 00:05:04,670
Just go!

100
00:05:05,130 --> 00:05:06,740
See what tricks he can pull!

101
00:05:07,980 --> 00:05:09,450
But I've never been to

102
00:05:09,480 --> 00:05:10,310
that kind of occasion.

103
00:05:10,310 --> 00:05:11,570
I don't know what to do.

104
00:05:11,870 --> 00:05:13,130
I really don't want to go.

105
00:05:13,130 --> 00:05:13,980
But if I don't,

106
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:14,540
I have no idea

107
00:05:14,540 --> 00:05:16,600
when the next opportunity will come.

108
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,110
If you should go, then go,

109
00:05:20,220 --> 00:05:20,690
right?

110
00:05:20,830 --> 00:05:22,300
Introduce yourself

111
00:05:22,360 --> 00:05:23,270
when it's time.

112
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:25,930
Hold your head high,

113
00:05:25,950 --> 00:05:26,430
right?

114
00:05:27,040 --> 00:05:27,970
We shouldn't

115
00:05:28,190 --> 00:05:29,060
bow or scrape.

116
00:05:29,430 --> 00:05:30,430
Zongbao is right.

117
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,220
Just be natural about it.

118
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:32,820
It's okay.

119
00:05:32,870 --> 00:05:33,480
Exactly.

120
00:05:33,630 --> 00:05:35,400
Don't imagine the worst.

121
00:05:35,740 --> 00:05:37,270
It might actually be a good opportunity.

122
00:05:37,270 --> 00:05:37,670
Right.

123
00:05:38,370 --> 00:05:39,430
If he really tries to
pull something on us,

124
00:05:39,430 --> 00:05:40,430
we can just leave.

125
00:05:40,450 --> 00:05:41,450
There are plenty of other chances.

126
00:05:41,450 --> 00:05:41,860
Yeah.

127
00:05:42,360 --> 00:05:43,330
Don't be afraid.

128
00:05:43,930 --> 00:05:45,240
Even if the sky falls,

129
00:05:45,720 --> 00:05:46,810
just tell me.

130
00:05:47,220 --> 00:05:48,280
I've got your back.

131
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:50,040
And me.

132
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:52,630
Anyway, wherever

133
00:05:52,630 --> 00:05:53,430
you need me,

134
00:05:53,450 --> 00:05:54,360
whether it's physical labor

135
00:05:54,360 --> 00:05:55,360
or anything else,

136
00:05:55,360 --> 00:05:56,240
just say the word.

137
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,830
I won't hesitate for a second.

138
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:58,290
Ranran,

139
00:05:59,450 --> 00:06:00,780
no matter what happens,

140
00:06:01,250 --> 00:06:02,710
as long as we keep smiling,

141
00:06:02,810 --> 00:06:03,800
we haven't lost.

142
00:06:04,570 --> 00:06:05,220
We've all

143
00:06:05,240 --> 00:06:06,630
got your back.

144
00:06:07,060 --> 00:06:07,460
Right.

145
00:06:09,000 --> 00:06:10,000
What do you think?

146
00:06:10,980 --> 00:06:11,370
Fine.

147
00:06:12,570 --> 00:06:13,330
I'll go.

148
00:06:13,950 --> 00:06:15,570
I believe I'm a good actress.

149
00:06:16,310 --> 00:06:17,250
I am the unbreakable

150
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:17,980
Wu Qinghua!

151
00:06:18,630 --> 00:06:19,480
I can do this.

152
00:06:19,720 --> 00:06:20,810
You definitely can!

153
00:06:20,810 --> 00:06:21,940
You definitely can!

154
00:06:26,810 --> 00:06:27,770
If that big investor

155
00:06:27,770 --> 00:06:28,600
rubs you the wrong way,

156
00:06:28,600 --> 00:06:29,930
come back immediately.

157
00:06:31,430 --> 00:06:32,360
Don't drink.

158
00:06:33,270 --> 00:06:35,670
Just say you're
taking care of your health.

159
00:06:35,810 --> 00:06:36,180
Okay.

160
00:06:43,370 --> 00:06:43,920
Mr. Zhou!

161
00:06:44,430 --> 00:06:45,560
Yes, it's me, Cao Ye!

162
00:06:46,890 --> 00:06:47,550
No problem!

163
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:48,180
I'm free!

164
00:06:48,190 --> 00:06:49,590
I can head over right now!

165
00:06:50,000 --> 00:06:51,040
It's about my paintings, right?

166
00:06:51,040 --> 00:06:52,040
They sold, right?

167
00:06:53,310 --> 00:06:54,240
Okay, okay.

168
00:06:54,330 --> 00:06:55,250
Let's talk details in person.

169
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:55,580
Okay.

170
00:07:00,950 --> 00:07:01,720
Good news?

171
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,740
Wait for me to come back.

172
00:07:06,740 --> 00:07:08,030
Pick any restaurant you want,

173
00:07:08,030 --> 00:07:08,560
my treat.

174
00:07:09,010 --> 00:07:10,270
A fortune is coming in.

175
00:07:10,420 --> 00:07:11,810
Fortune or not, it's all just

176
00:07:11,810 --> 00:07:12,890
worldly possessions, right?

177
00:07:12,890 --> 00:07:13,430
Can you use

178
00:07:13,430 --> 00:07:14,330
those worldly possessions

179
00:07:14,330 --> 00:07:15,930
to pay the rent you owe first?

180
00:07:16,190 --> 00:07:17,310
They're not in my possession yet.

181
00:07:17,310 --> 00:07:18,250
Wait until I get back.

182
00:07:18,250 --> 00:07:19,390
Forget about the overdue rent,

183
00:07:19,390 --> 00:07:21,250
I'll pay for a whole year upfront!

184
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:22,810
See? What did I say?

185
00:07:23,480 --> 00:07:25,810
You're never meant to
stay in a small pond.

186
00:07:26,010 --> 00:07:26,870
Let me teach you one more time.

187
00:07:26,870 --> 00:07:27,870
Keep this in mind.

188
00:07:28,220 --> 00:07:30,680
A golden-scaled fish was never meant to
stay in a pond;

189
00:07:30,680 --> 00:07:33,250
when the winds and clouds stir,
it transforms into a dragon!

190
00:07:33,250 --> 00:07:34,850
You've turned into a dragon!

191
00:07:35,600 --> 00:07:37,260
I'm going to my room to change.

192
00:07:37,300 --> 00:07:38,560
You, help me hail a cab.

193
00:07:38,720 --> 00:07:40,520
We're moving up in the world now!

194
00:07:41,220 --> 00:07:42,820
Help me pay for the cab first.

195
00:07:43,750 --> 00:07:45,680
I'll pay you double when I get back.

196
00:07:46,270 --> 00:07:47,000
Got it!

197
00:07:49,100 --> 00:07:50,190
This was the expert dorm

198
00:07:50,190 --> 00:07:51,240
back at our studio.

199
00:07:51,240 --> 00:07:51,750
Director Weng,

200
00:07:51,750 --> 00:07:53,409
would such a master accept me?

201
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:54,810
We're already here.

202
00:07:54,810 --> 00:07:56,010
Don't talk nonsense.

203
00:07:56,740 --> 00:07:57,860
Let me put it this way.

204
00:07:57,860 --> 00:07:58,890
I think

205
00:07:59,000 --> 00:08:00,460
your handwriting is good.

206
00:08:00,860 --> 00:08:02,190
It might catch his eye.

207
00:08:03,690 --> 00:08:05,220
It's also because you've got it on you.

208
00:08:05,220 --> 00:08:06,060
If you were no good,

209
00:08:06,060 --> 00:08:08,320
I'd be too embarrassed to recommend you.

210
00:08:08,420 --> 00:08:10,010
Let me say the hard part first.

211
00:08:10,010 --> 00:08:11,270
Hello, Director Weng.

212
00:08:12,620 --> 00:08:14,280
Let me say the hard part first.

213
00:08:15,740 --> 00:08:17,540
Whether it goes well or not

214
00:08:18,450 --> 00:08:19,430
depends on you.

215
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:20,800
Don't worry.

216
00:08:20,830 --> 00:08:21,800
I'll do whatever it takes

217
00:08:21,800 --> 00:08:22,660
to get him to take me on.

218
00:08:22,660 --> 00:08:22,990
Good.

219
00:08:27,180 --> 00:08:28,920
There're scissors, glue,

220
00:08:29,130 --> 00:08:30,160
and carbon paper in here.

221
00:08:30,160 --> 00:08:31,130
I've prepared everything

222
00:08:31,130 --> 00:08:31,990
I could for you.

223
00:08:32,340 --> 00:08:34,400
These are tools I used back in the day.

224
00:08:35,440 --> 00:08:36,900
Thank you, Director Weng.

225
00:08:38,980 --> 00:08:39,500
Listen,

226
00:08:39,530 --> 00:08:41,150
if he does take you on,

227
00:08:41,650 --> 00:08:43,200
you must learn from him properly.

228
00:08:43,200 --> 00:08:44,660
Definitely. Definitely.

229
00:08:59,340 --> 00:08:59,810
See?

230
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:03,120
Sleeping in broad daylight
with the door unlocked.

231
00:09:03,120 --> 00:09:04,980
He's waiting to swindle someone.

232
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:11,630
I was just

233
00:09:12,250 --> 00:09:14,980
dreaming about a key plot point
for the script...

234
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:22,100
and you woke me up.

235
00:09:22,980 --> 00:09:25,180
I don't care! I've brought the man here!

236
00:09:25,460 --> 00:09:26,520
I won't see you out.

237
00:09:29,960 --> 00:09:30,620
No, wait...

238
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:31,530
You stay...

239
00:09:37,960 --> 00:09:38,820
Hello, mentor.

240
00:09:39,600 --> 00:09:40,800
My name is Xu Shengli.

241
00:09:40,940 --> 00:09:41,870
Xu, spelled X-U.

242
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,550
Shengli as in "Shengli Oilfield."

243
00:09:43,550 --> 00:09:44,210
Okay, okay.

244
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,870
Don't give me that whole spiel.

245
00:10:25,150 --> 00:10:26,480
How does it smell to you?

246
00:10:27,220 --> 00:10:28,600
The stink of alcohol, eh?

247
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,330
It's the fragrance of alcohol.

248
00:10:32,910 --> 00:10:34,240
A sweet-talking man...

249
00:10:35,360 --> 00:10:38,120
I'd better watch out for you.

250
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,700
It smells rough but tastes great.

251
00:10:48,130 --> 00:10:49,630
Good, good.

252
00:10:51,270 --> 00:10:53,270
You've smoothed things over.

253
00:10:56,580 --> 00:10:59,320
I can't find anything
to criticize about you, huh?

254
00:10:59,320 --> 00:11:00,370
Go! Get out!

255
00:11:00,600 --> 00:11:02,340
Get out! Go! Get out!

256
00:11:02,770 --> 00:11:03,830
Mr... Mr. He, um...

257
00:11:12,150 --> 00:11:13,430
Coming, coming.

258
00:11:13,940 --> 00:11:14,610
Wait a second!

259
00:11:14,610 --> 00:11:15,670
Wait, wait.

260
00:11:15,980 --> 00:11:18,320
Come on, hurry, come back and sit!

261
00:11:18,340 --> 00:11:19,580
Hurry! Come on and sit!

262
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:20,580
Sit! Sit down!

263
00:11:20,860 --> 00:11:21,580
Pen, pen.

264
00:11:21,720 --> 00:11:22,320
Come here.

265
00:11:23,220 --> 00:11:24,440
Sit here! Here!

266
00:11:24,580 --> 00:11:25,240
Right here!

267
00:11:25,870 --> 00:11:26,600
Take the pen.

268
00:11:26,860 --> 00:11:28,460
I'll dictate, and you write.

269
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:30,600
Hurry up! Hurry!

270
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:32,600
An abandoned factory...

271
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:34,000
An abandoned factory...

272
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:36,320
Night. Summer, summer.

273
00:11:35,780 --> 00:11:38,060
[An abandoned factory, night, summer]

274
00:11:38,650 --> 00:11:41,530
Dark clouds... cover the moon.

275
00:11:43,440 --> 00:11:45,980
The wind howls,

276
00:11:44,270 --> 00:11:48,310
[The clouds cover the moon. The wind.]

277
00:11:46,790 --> 00:11:49,220
and the leaves shake violently.

278
00:11:50,080 --> 00:11:50,880
Write faster.

279
00:11:51,220 --> 00:11:52,390
Shake violently...

280
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,310
At this moment,

281
00:11:54,360 --> 00:11:55,090
suddenly...

282
00:11:56,620 --> 00:11:59,870
a little stray cat appears.

283
00:12:00,170 --> 00:12:00,960
Mr. He, could you

284
00:12:00,960 --> 00:12:01,910
speak a little slower?

285
00:12:01,910 --> 00:12:03,440
You need to write faster!

286
00:12:03,620 --> 00:12:04,550
You... you're speaking Sichuan dialect,

287
00:12:04,550 --> 00:12:05,840
and I... I need time to process it.

288
00:12:05,840 --> 00:12:06,530
Sichuan dialect?

289
00:12:06,530 --> 00:12:08,170
I'm speaking Mandarin!

290
00:12:09,460 --> 00:12:10,320
Where were you?

291
00:12:11,130 --> 00:12:12,740
I wrote to wind... leaves... wind...

292
00:12:12,740 --> 00:12:13,120
To...

293
00:12:13,250 --> 00:12:14,740
A little stray cat appears!

294
00:12:14,740 --> 00:12:16,980
A little stray cat... a little stray cat.

295
00:12:16,980 --> 00:12:18,310
The little stray cat...

296
00:12:19,050 --> 00:12:23,010
tiptoes into the factory building.

297
00:12:23,460 --> 00:12:26,510
Shadows flicker across the building.

298
00:12:26,700 --> 00:12:27,960
Suddenly, a scream!

299
00:12:30,720 --> 00:12:32,300
Who moved my chair,

300
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:32,750
huh?

301
00:12:33,340 --> 00:12:33,770
Who?

302
00:12:33,840 --> 00:12:34,480
I... I...

303
00:12:34,530 --> 00:12:35,500
I moved it over just now.

304
00:12:35,500 --> 00:12:36,170
I thought I'd sit there.

305
00:12:36,170 --> 00:12:37,100
Move it back!

306
00:12:37,150 --> 00:12:38,990
Move it back for me! Move it back!

307
00:12:41,750 --> 00:12:42,560
Move it back!

308
00:12:44,510 --> 00:12:45,020
Right.

309
00:12:45,150 --> 00:12:47,250
Don't let it happen again.

310
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:49,840
Sit back. Sit.

311
00:12:53,860 --> 00:12:55,180
For us screenwriters,

312
00:12:55,460 --> 00:12:57,650
the most important thing is inspiration.

313
00:12:57,650 --> 00:12:59,440
Inspiration is like a ghost.

314
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:02,450
You don't know when it will come

315
00:13:02,740 --> 00:13:04,340
or when it will leave.

316
00:13:04,790 --> 00:13:05,650
It's fleeting.

317
00:13:05,790 --> 00:13:06,920
You have to catch it.

318
00:13:09,120 --> 00:13:10,320
On this desk

319
00:13:10,500 --> 00:13:12,410
are the scripts I wrote.

320
00:13:12,960 --> 00:13:14,940
They are part of my creation.

321
00:13:17,870 --> 00:13:18,650
My...

322
00:13:19,890 --> 00:13:21,550
my eyes are always so worn out.

323
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:23,570
So I need someone

324
00:13:23,860 --> 00:13:25,320
to help me copy my scripts.

325
00:13:25,630 --> 00:13:27,090
Your handwriting is nice.

326
00:13:27,750 --> 00:13:29,120
I think you'll be of use.

327
00:13:30,790 --> 00:13:33,190
Since you're going to work here,

328
00:13:33,510 --> 00:13:34,990
first of all,

329
00:13:35,630 --> 00:13:37,170
let's set the ground rules.

330
00:13:37,910 --> 00:13:38,530
First,

331
00:13:40,240 --> 00:13:41,660
in this room,

332
00:13:41,960 --> 00:13:43,060
nothing

333
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:44,700
can be touched.

334
00:13:45,480 --> 00:13:47,410
Don't move anything, even an inch.

335
00:13:47,460 --> 00:13:48,260
Do you hear me?

336
00:13:48,600 --> 00:13:48,940
Okay.

337
00:13:49,340 --> 00:13:50,220
Second...

338
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:53,370
Pour me a cup of water.

339
00:13:53,370 --> 00:13:54,570
Pour me a cup of water.

340
00:13:56,290 --> 00:13:56,740
Right.

341
00:13:58,150 --> 00:13:58,620
Over there.

342
00:13:58,620 --> 00:13:59,890
Yes, there. That's it.

343
00:14:00,500 --> 00:14:01,560
Pour me some water.

344
00:14:07,000 --> 00:14:09,120
-An abandoned factory...
-Mr. He, water.

345
00:14:09,120 --> 00:14:09,520
Water.

346
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:11,530
This is the second rule.

347
00:14:12,750 --> 00:14:14,980
When I wake up,

348
00:14:15,790 --> 00:14:17,420
you pour me a cup of water.

349
00:14:17,620 --> 00:14:18,480
Okay, got it.

350
00:14:18,960 --> 00:14:20,100
Sit down. Sit.

351
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:20,790
Sit.

352
00:14:28,410 --> 00:14:29,240
And third,

353
00:14:30,100 --> 00:14:30,770
you have to

354
00:14:31,080 --> 00:14:32,030
stay

355
00:14:32,220 --> 00:14:33,500
in this room all day.

356
00:14:34,770 --> 00:14:36,440
You can only leave

357
00:14:36,530 --> 00:14:37,680
when I say so.

358
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:38,810
Understand?

359
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:40,300
Understand, understand.

360
00:14:40,440 --> 00:14:42,290
So I'll be here all day?

361
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:45,770
Then w-will you provide three meals a day?

362
00:14:46,940 --> 00:14:47,620
You idiot.

363
00:14:48,460 --> 00:14:49,790
This isn't a cafeteria.

364
00:14:50,510 --> 00:14:52,250
I only cover lunch.

365
00:14:52,370 --> 00:14:53,030
No problem.

366
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:54,700
I'd do it even without meals.

367
00:14:56,170 --> 00:14:57,010
Let me tell you

368
00:14:57,250 --> 00:14:58,650
how to handle newcomers.

369
00:14:58,770 --> 00:14:59,680
Newcomers

370
00:14:59,750 --> 00:15:01,350
are like grass in the spring.

371
00:15:02,200 --> 00:15:03,030
You never know

372
00:15:03,030 --> 00:15:04,270
which sprout will bloom

373
00:15:04,270 --> 00:15:05,370
and which won't.

374
00:15:05,750 --> 00:15:06,320
So,

375
00:15:06,460 --> 00:15:07,960
you have to give them more sunshine

376
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:09,090
and water them more.

377
00:15:09,290 --> 00:15:10,270
When the spring breeze blows,

378
00:15:10,270 --> 00:15:11,730
you'll know immediately.

379
00:15:13,080 --> 00:15:13,480
What?

380
00:15:13,940 --> 00:15:15,620
What are sunshine and water?

381
00:15:16,630 --> 00:15:17,340
Money!

382
00:15:18,550 --> 00:15:19,630
Investment!

383
00:15:21,670 --> 00:15:22,100
Right.

384
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:24,530
Our money is the sunshine

385
00:15:24,550 --> 00:15:25,320
and water.

386
00:15:25,770 --> 00:15:26,700
Who are we?

387
00:15:26,980 --> 00:15:28,180
We're the investors.

388
00:15:30,250 --> 00:15:31,050
Let's do this—

389
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:32,000
once you've picked the actors,

390
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:32,930
bring them to me.

391
00:15:33,150 --> 00:15:34,350
I'll vet them for you.

392
00:15:37,080 --> 00:15:37,620
You're here!

393
00:15:37,620 --> 00:15:38,130
Mr. Chu,

394
00:15:38,370 --> 00:15:39,980
really, I haven't even
had a proper word with you yet,

395
00:15:39,980 --> 00:15:40,440
and you've

396
00:15:40,440 --> 00:15:41,840
already enlightened me.

397
00:15:42,740 --> 00:15:44,250
Not at all. That was a friend of mine.

398
00:15:44,250 --> 00:15:45,500
He wants to invest in film and TV too.

399
00:15:45,500 --> 00:15:47,500
I was just giving him some pointers.

400
00:15:49,290 --> 00:15:50,480
Let me introduce you.

401
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:50,940
Ranran,

402
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:51,550
this is

403
00:15:51,600 --> 00:15:52,900
the famous Mr. Chu.

404
00:15:53,120 --> 00:15:53,580
Mr. Chu,

405
00:15:53,840 --> 00:15:54,530
this is the actress

406
00:15:54,530 --> 00:15:55,690
I mentioned before—

407
00:15:55,820 --> 00:15:56,550
Shen Ranran.

408
00:15:58,030 --> 00:15:59,720
Okay. Good, good.

409
00:16:02,670 --> 00:16:04,330
Well, don't just stand there.

410
00:16:04,580 --> 00:16:05,310
Let's go eat.

411
00:16:06,170 --> 00:16:06,630
Mr. Chu,

412
00:16:06,670 --> 00:16:07,650
I'm really sorry.

413
00:16:07,650 --> 00:16:09,290
I thought we'd just chat for a bit.

414
00:16:09,290 --> 00:16:10,030
In a little while,

415
00:16:10,030 --> 00:16:12,010
I have to go pick up a relative
at the train station.

416
00:16:12,010 --> 00:16:12,470
Well...

417
00:16:13,080 --> 00:16:13,610
Why don't

418
00:16:14,080 --> 00:16:15,810
you two go ahead and have lunch?

419
00:16:21,860 --> 00:16:22,440
Shen,

420
00:16:23,010 --> 00:16:24,070
where are you from?

421
00:16:24,200 --> 00:16:24,750
Huzhou.

422
00:16:26,080 --> 00:16:27,210
You're from Huzhou.

423
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:28,980
Huzhou is a nice place.

424
00:16:30,340 --> 00:16:30,940
Waitress,

425
00:16:31,720 --> 00:16:33,410
do you have any Huzhou cuisine here?

426
00:16:33,410 --> 00:16:33,870
Sir,

427
00:16:33,910 --> 00:16:35,170
at the Siji Kang Grand Hotel,

428
00:16:35,170 --> 00:16:36,480
you can find dishes
from all over the country.

429
00:16:36,480 --> 00:16:37,630
Talk is cheap.

430
00:16:39,410 --> 00:16:40,340
I'm telling you,

431
00:16:40,460 --> 00:16:41,590
this guest next to me

432
00:16:41,870 --> 00:16:42,730
is from Huzhou.

433
00:16:42,910 --> 00:16:43,820
I want to know

434
00:16:44,270 --> 00:16:45,200
if your dishes

435
00:16:45,620 --> 00:16:46,480
are authentic.

436
00:16:46,910 --> 00:16:47,770
If they're not,

437
00:16:48,150 --> 00:16:49,010
I'm not paying.

438
00:16:51,220 --> 00:16:52,320
It's my honor to invite you here

439
00:16:52,320 --> 00:16:53,180
for a meal.

440
00:16:53,390 --> 00:16:55,190
Please order whatever you like.

441
00:16:55,600 --> 00:16:56,460
Don't say that.

442
00:16:56,510 --> 00:16:57,440
It's just a meal.

443
00:16:57,910 --> 00:16:58,680
Besides,

444
00:16:59,010 --> 00:17:00,140
for actors like you,

445
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:02,130
it's not easy making it in Beijing.

446
00:17:03,250 --> 00:17:03,970
Well,

447
00:17:04,220 --> 00:17:05,109
I'd like

448
00:17:05,109 --> 00:17:06,349
a Stewed Shredded Eel.

449
00:17:06,349 --> 00:17:07,480
I want the eel to be freshly killed.

450
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:09,140
Have Chef Liu make it himself.

451
00:17:09,510 --> 00:17:10,300
Then...

452
00:17:10,440 --> 00:17:12,040
a serving of Tofu Skin Rolls.

453
00:17:12,220 --> 00:17:14,150
A Drunken Fish and Crispy Pork Pot.

454
00:17:14,510 --> 00:17:15,790
Do you have any Choy Sum in season today?

455
00:17:15,790 --> 00:17:16,089
Yes.

456
00:17:16,660 --> 00:17:17,460
That's great.

457
00:17:18,109 --> 00:17:19,400
These hutong alleys are so winding.

458
00:17:19,400 --> 00:17:20,440
Where on earth is this place?

459
00:17:20,440 --> 00:17:22,099
You're living so deep inside.

460
00:17:22,980 --> 00:17:24,000
Are we there yet?

461
00:17:25,920 --> 00:17:26,900
Are we there yet?

462
00:17:29,980 --> 00:17:31,090
Where? Here?

463
00:17:31,900 --> 00:17:32,920
You should've said something.

464
00:17:32,920 --> 00:17:33,880
I was still pedaling forward!

465
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:35,140
You're unbelievable.

466
00:17:35,530 --> 00:17:36,180
Making this little bit of money off you

467
00:17:36,180 --> 00:17:37,510
is hard work, honestly.

468
00:17:38,270 --> 00:17:39,050
My goodness.

469
00:17:40,620 --> 00:17:46,610
[Seasons Change Hostel]

470
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,510
What? What are you doing?

471
00:17:42,510 --> 00:17:43,420
Pay up.

472
00:17:45,140 --> 00:17:46,940
How much did we agree on earlier?

473
00:17:47,480 --> 00:17:48,880
Didn't we already agree?

474
00:17:49,030 --> 00:17:50,230
It was such a long way.

475
00:17:50,270 --> 00:17:50,900
Five yuan.

476
00:17:51,090 --> 00:17:57,420
[Seasons Change Hostel]

477
00:17:55,030 --> 00:17:55,460
Sir,

478
00:17:55,960 --> 00:17:57,420
my name is Cao Ye.

479
00:17:58,200 --> 00:17:59,140
I'm a painter.

480
00:18:00,110 --> 00:18:02,070
You saw for yourself where I brought

481
00:18:02,070 --> 00:18:03,330
these paintings from.

482
00:18:04,480 --> 00:18:05,770
I'll give you a painting.

483
00:18:05,770 --> 00:18:07,110
When I become famous one day,

484
00:18:07,110 --> 00:18:09,240
that painting will be worth a fortune.

485
00:18:09,240 --> 00:18:10,530
"Worth a fortune?"

486
00:18:10,550 --> 00:18:11,570
You can't even scrape together five yuan,

487
00:18:11,570 --> 00:18:13,220
and you're talking to me about fortunes?

488
00:18:13,220 --> 00:18:16,520
[Seasons Change Hostel]

489
00:18:13,570 --> 00:18:14,770
What's all the noise?

490
00:18:17,700 --> 00:18:18,900
What's going on here?

491
00:18:22,570 --> 00:18:24,570
You're moving down in the world, eh?

492
00:18:26,140 --> 00:18:28,340
We just turned into a dragon, didn't we?

493
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:31,850
Why are you looking at me like that?

494
00:18:32,010 --> 00:18:32,570
Dragon.

495
00:18:35,380 --> 00:18:36,140
Lend me five yuan first

496
00:18:36,140 --> 00:18:37,240
so I can settle the fare.

497
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:38,370
Put it on my room tab.

498
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:40,010
Well, when you left,

499
00:18:40,010 --> 00:18:41,050
I paid 30 yuan

500
00:18:41,070 --> 00:18:41,980
for your taxi!

501
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:44,060
Now you want another five yuan?

502
00:18:44,940 --> 00:18:45,940
I have other gigs out there,

503
00:18:45,940 --> 00:18:46,610
you know that.

504
00:18:46,610 --> 00:18:48,420
I'll pay you everything once I get paid.

505
00:18:48,420 --> 00:18:49,400
Mr. Cao,

506
00:18:49,420 --> 00:18:50,500
how much rent do you owe—

507
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:52,110
don't you have a clue yourself?

508
00:18:52,110 --> 00:18:53,350
You keep saying, "Pay me everything."

509
00:18:53,350 --> 00:18:54,850
But when are you actually going to pay me?

510
00:18:54,850 --> 00:18:56,220
Tomorrow. I'll definitely pay tomorrow.

511
00:18:56,220 --> 00:18:57,610
You keep saying "tomorrow!"

512
00:18:57,610 --> 00:18:58,940
Can I even count on that?

513
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:00,770
If you two want to argue,

514
00:19:00,770 --> 00:19:01,990
go do it inside.

515
00:19:02,270 --> 00:19:03,530
I've been standing here waiting forever.

516
00:19:03,530 --> 00:19:04,900
Don't you try to take advantage of
an honest man!

517
00:19:04,900 --> 00:19:05,830
Hurry up and pay!

518
00:19:08,180 --> 00:19:09,180
Northeasterner,

519
00:19:11,240 --> 00:19:12,170
I'm begging you.

520
00:19:12,740 --> 00:19:13,960
I mean, you two grown men

521
00:19:13,960 --> 00:19:15,200
don't have five yuan?

522
00:19:17,660 --> 00:19:18,350
We'll pay!

523
00:19:18,750 --> 00:19:20,610
It's just five yuan! I'll pay you!

524
00:19:23,700 --> 00:19:25,030
When Cui approached me,

525
00:19:25,110 --> 00:19:26,030
I considered it

526
00:19:27,460 --> 00:19:29,190
and finally agreed to meet you.

527
00:19:29,310 --> 00:19:30,180
Mainly because

528
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:31,370
there are things

529
00:19:31,400 --> 00:19:32,530
I want to explain

530
00:19:32,790 --> 00:19:33,720
to you in person.

531
00:19:33,830 --> 00:19:35,480
Are you talking about that role?

532
00:19:35,480 --> 00:19:36,700
Director Cui told me.

533
00:19:36,850 --> 00:19:38,420
He said you're the investor

534
00:19:38,460 --> 00:19:39,390
in this project.

535
00:19:39,460 --> 00:19:40,120
One of them.

536
00:19:41,110 --> 00:19:42,510
I'm one of the investors.

537
00:19:44,570 --> 00:19:45,900
I'll be honest with you.

538
00:19:46,290 --> 00:19:47,500
Even though I'm an investor

539
00:19:47,500 --> 00:19:48,230
in this show,

540
00:19:48,720 --> 00:19:50,120
when it comes to casting,

541
00:19:50,440 --> 00:19:51,440
I don't have a say.

542
00:19:51,960 --> 00:19:53,290
How does that saying go?

543
00:19:53,530 --> 00:19:54,330
"Leave professional matters

544
00:19:54,330 --> 00:19:55,700
to professionals."

545
00:19:56,590 --> 00:19:57,700
As for casting,

546
00:19:57,900 --> 00:19:59,880
we have to let the director handle it.

547
00:19:59,880 --> 00:20:00,460
In short,

548
00:20:00,480 --> 00:20:01,810
what I'm trying to say is

549
00:20:01,940 --> 00:20:04,220
that everything is
for the sake of the show.

550
00:20:04,220 --> 00:20:06,110
Good casting makes a good show.

551
00:20:06,570 --> 00:20:07,220
A good show

552
00:20:07,610 --> 00:20:08,940
means we all make money.

553
00:20:09,240 --> 00:20:10,270
You see, these days,

554
00:20:10,270 --> 00:20:11,010
no one would let

555
00:20:11,010 --> 00:20:12,270
personal preferences

556
00:20:12,660 --> 00:20:13,900
tank their own production

557
00:20:13,900 --> 00:20:15,400
and lose money, right?

558
00:20:17,110 --> 00:20:17,680
Right.

559
00:20:18,310 --> 00:20:19,250
You're right.

560
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:21,660
But before,

561
00:20:21,770 --> 00:20:22,770
Director Cui did cast me

562
00:20:22,770 --> 00:20:23,810
in that role.

563
00:20:25,110 --> 00:20:27,240
Now that I've been suddenly replaced,

564
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,400
I can't help feeling upset about it.

565
00:20:30,250 --> 00:20:31,050
I understand.

566
00:20:32,140 --> 00:20:34,000
Replacing actors before filming

567
00:20:34,140 --> 00:20:34,940
isn't common,

568
00:20:35,420 --> 00:20:36,480
but it does happen.

569
00:20:37,030 --> 00:20:38,630
So don't take it personally.

570
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:40,480
Maybe because that was my

571
00:20:40,480 --> 00:20:41,610
first opportunity,

572
00:20:42,400 --> 00:20:43,460
it meant a lot to me.

573
00:20:46,350 --> 00:20:48,550
That was your first opportunity, true.

574
00:20:48,790 --> 00:20:50,320
But it can't be the only one.

575
00:20:50,810 --> 00:20:51,330
You see,

576
00:20:52,030 --> 00:20:53,270
an actress like you—

577
00:20:53,550 --> 00:20:54,200
young,

578
00:20:54,500 --> 00:20:55,980
with little life experience

579
00:20:55,980 --> 00:20:57,640
and no connections to speak of—

580
00:20:57,640 --> 00:21:00,100
really does need someone
to give her a leg up.

581
00:21:00,400 --> 00:21:01,260
How about this?

582
00:21:01,550 --> 00:21:02,410
I'll do my best.

583
00:21:04,920 --> 00:21:06,520
If you're willing to help me,

584
00:21:07,220 --> 00:21:08,750
I'd be extremely grateful.

585
00:21:08,770 --> 00:21:10,140
Don't thank me yet.

586
00:21:10,740 --> 00:21:11,940
When I saw your headshot,

587
00:21:11,940 --> 00:21:13,070
I thought to myself,

588
00:21:13,250 --> 00:21:14,450
such a beautiful girl

589
00:21:14,610 --> 00:21:15,880
is bound to make it big sooner or later

590
00:21:15,880 --> 00:21:16,960
in this industry.

591
00:21:17,420 --> 00:21:19,140
I'd better watch myself around you now—

592
00:21:19,140 --> 00:21:20,240
can't afford to get on your bad side.

593
00:21:20,240 --> 00:21:21,850
If you become a star one day

594
00:21:22,070 --> 00:21:23,010
and badmouth me in the industry,

595
00:21:23,010 --> 00:21:24,870
I wouldn't be able to handle that.

596
00:21:30,830 --> 00:21:37,540
[Public Phone; Long-Distance Service]

597
00:21:31,200 --> 00:21:31,750
Mr. Lyu.

598
00:21:32,070 --> 00:21:33,270
Yeah, yeah. I'm good.

599
00:21:33,660 --> 00:21:34,720
You doing well too?

600
00:21:36,830 --> 00:21:38,830
Well... there's just a small thing.

601
00:21:39,070 --> 00:21:41,830
Well, I recently took on a gig,

602
00:21:41,850 --> 00:21:43,450
but they haven't paid me yet.

603
00:21:43,660 --> 00:21:45,390
So I was wondering if I could...

604
00:21:46,240 --> 00:21:48,110
borrow 50 from you first.

605
00:21:48,850 --> 00:21:49,790
Once I get paid for this gig,

606
00:21:49,790 --> 00:21:50,990
I'll immediately...

607
00:21:51,480 --> 00:21:52,080
Mr. Lyu...

608
00:21:52,160 --> 00:21:52,570
Hello?

609
00:21:58,140 --> 00:22:04,220
[Public Phone; Long-Distance Service]

610
00:22:15,700 --> 00:22:16,400
Zhao?

611
00:22:17,850 --> 00:22:19,160
Zhao, Mr. Zhao!

612
00:22:20,030 --> 00:22:21,000
It's me, Cao Ye.

613
00:22:23,010 --> 00:22:24,870
Suddenly thought of you? Come on!

614
00:22:25,110 --> 00:22:26,290
I've always been thinking of you.

615
00:22:26,290 --> 00:22:27,400
Not just now.

616
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:31,240
No, n-nothing serious. Just...

617
00:22:32,350 --> 00:22:34,220
I took on a gig recently,

618
00:22:34,880 --> 00:22:36,220
but haven't gotten paid yet.

619
00:22:36,220 --> 00:22:37,010
I'm a bit tight on cash.

620
00:22:37,010 --> 00:22:38,610
I was wondering if I could...

621
00:22:38,750 --> 00:22:40,550
borrow 30 from you first.

622
00:22:43,350 --> 00:22:44,290
Had a surgery?

623
00:22:45,440 --> 00:22:46,250
When did that happen?

624
00:22:46,250 --> 00:22:47,850
Wait, what... what illness?

625
00:22:48,900 --> 00:22:49,830
Mr. Zhao, you...

626
00:22:50,900 --> 00:22:51,560
Mr. Zhao...

627
00:22:54,020 --> 00:22:58,870
[Public Phone; Long-Distance Service]

628
00:22:59,420 --> 00:23:00,950
Just leave the money there.

629
00:23:04,380 --> 00:23:04,940
What?

630
00:23:05,350 --> 00:23:06,770
Don't tell me you didn't bring any money.

631
00:23:06,770 --> 00:23:07,400
I... I...

632
00:23:08,270 --> 00:23:10,400
Keep calling if you haven't finished yet.

633
00:23:10,400 --> 00:23:10,810
Yeah.

634
00:23:15,880 --> 00:23:17,490
W-When I came here,

635
00:23:17,720 --> 00:23:19,400
my shoes kept slipping off.

636
00:23:19,440 --> 00:23:20,370
My shoelaces...

637
00:23:30,850 --> 00:23:32,220
Room and board included.

638
00:23:32,220 --> 00:23:33,750
Would you like to join

639
00:23:33,750 --> 00:23:34,900
our big family?

640
00:25:05,850 --> 00:25:07,310
It's enough. It's enough!

641
00:25:14,850 --> 00:25:15,250
Dad.

642
00:25:16,350 --> 00:25:17,080
Don't worry.

643
00:25:17,980 --> 00:25:18,940
With my skills,

644
00:25:19,880 --> 00:25:22,880
I'll definitely
make something of myself in Beijing.

645
00:25:26,460 --> 00:25:28,390
Just take care of yourself at home.

646
00:25:28,400 --> 00:25:30,330
Wait for me to bring you to Beijing.

647
00:26:01,380 --> 00:26:01,910
Alright.

648
00:26:05,200 --> 00:26:05,800
This is it.

649
00:26:48,940 --> 00:26:50,070
Knife-cut noodles!

650
00:26:51,030 --> 00:26:52,140
Cao, what...

651
00:26:57,110 --> 00:26:57,750
Cao?

652
00:27:19,180 --> 00:27:21,350
Cao... What happened?

653
00:27:23,500 --> 00:27:24,550
This afternoon,

654
00:27:24,960 --> 00:27:25,530
he hauled back

655
00:27:25,530 --> 00:27:26,660
all those paintings

656
00:27:26,660 --> 00:27:27,640
he'd taken out to sell

657
00:27:27,640 --> 00:27:29,700
and asked me
to find a place to store them.

658
00:27:29,700 --> 00:27:30,480
I just finished

659
00:27:30,480 --> 00:27:31,810
helping him put everything away,

660
00:27:31,810 --> 00:27:33,000
and when I came back, he was gone.

661
00:27:33,000 --> 00:27:33,660
Well, he...

662
00:27:33,720 --> 00:27:36,000
He didn't even s-say goodbye?

663
00:27:36,310 --> 00:27:37,370
He still owes rent.

664
00:27:38,030 --> 00:27:39,760
And I even covered his cab fare.

665
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:42,180
He really is a heretic.

666
00:27:45,570 --> 00:27:48,170
At least he had the conscience
to make noodles.

667
00:27:57,570 --> 00:28:00,770
Oh, ocean, ocean...

668
00:28:01,680 --> 00:28:03,210
What's with these noodles?

669
00:28:04,530 --> 00:28:05,140
Cao.

670
00:28:10,750 --> 00:28:11,210
Well...

671
00:28:11,960 --> 00:28:12,820
Where did he go?

672
00:28:13,070 --> 00:28:13,570
No idea.

673
00:28:14,680 --> 00:28:15,740
Just made everyone

674
00:28:16,740 --> 00:28:18,340
a bowl of knife-cut noodles.

675
00:28:22,960 --> 00:28:23,890
Let's eat, then.

676
00:28:25,050 --> 00:28:26,710
Or the noodles will get soggy.

677
00:28:27,050 --> 00:28:27,780
You go ahead.

678
00:28:29,140 --> 00:28:30,600
I don't have the appetite.

679
00:29:06,090 --> 00:29:07,160
You made noodles.

680
00:29:08,500 --> 00:29:09,320
Great.

681
00:29:09,570 --> 00:29:11,250
So nice to come home to a meal waiting.

682
00:29:11,250 --> 00:29:12,200
Cao Ye made them.

683
00:29:15,740 --> 00:29:16,540
What's wrong?

684
00:29:17,530 --> 00:29:18,740
Cao Ye left.

685
00:29:19,720 --> 00:29:20,640
He made a bowl of noodles for each of us

686
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:21,550
before he went.

687
00:29:36,880 --> 00:29:37,810
Are you alright?

688
00:29:39,090 --> 00:29:41,510
You won't leave, will you?

689
00:29:41,960 --> 00:29:42,790
No, I won't.

690
00:29:44,110 --> 00:29:45,510
There, there. Don't cry.

691
00:30:09,080 --> 00:30:18,230
[Seasons Change Hostel]

692
00:30:23,530 --> 00:30:25,070
Ma'am, a steamer of buns

693
00:30:25,070 --> 00:30:26,030
and a bowl of soybean milk.

694
00:30:26,030 --> 00:30:26,960
Coming right up.

695
00:30:33,850 --> 00:30:35,030
Meat or vegetarian?

696
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:35,550
Meat.

697
00:30:37,510 --> 00:30:38,190
Mr. Xu?

698
00:30:38,750 --> 00:30:39,610
Zhuang Zhuang?

699
00:30:39,830 --> 00:30:40,630
Just got back?

700
00:30:40,980 --> 00:30:42,380
Where are you going so early?

701
00:30:42,380 --> 00:30:43,090
Going to class.

702
00:30:43,090 --> 00:30:43,970
Have you eaten?

703
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:44,610
No.

704
00:30:44,880 --> 00:30:46,480
Then sit down and eat with me.

705
00:30:49,140 --> 00:30:50,640
Come on, it won't take long.

706
00:30:50,640 --> 00:30:51,970
Come on, sit. Have some.

707
00:30:52,960 --> 00:30:53,310
Okay.

708
00:30:54,140 --> 00:30:54,830
Ma'am,

709
00:30:55,000 --> 00:30:55,610
one more steamer of buns

710
00:30:55,610 --> 00:30:56,200
and a bowl of soybean milk.

711
00:30:56,200 --> 00:30:56,800
Coming up.

712
00:30:59,980 --> 00:31:01,000
Give it to her first.

713
00:31:01,000 --> 00:31:01,640
Thank you.

714
00:31:03,500 --> 00:31:05,300
Why is your class so early today?

715
00:31:05,780 --> 00:31:06,590
Recently, Mr. Zheng

716
00:31:06,590 --> 00:31:08,380
has only had time in the mornings.

717
00:31:08,380 --> 00:31:10,780
And I have to get up early
to warm up my voice.

718
00:31:13,500 --> 00:31:14,530
Okay, thanks.

719
00:31:15,380 --> 00:31:16,850
How are your lessons going?

720
00:31:16,850 --> 00:31:18,180
Pulled an all-nighter?

721
00:31:19,250 --> 00:31:20,220
Mr. He says

722
00:31:21,180 --> 00:31:22,780
inspiration is like a ghost—

723
00:31:22,870 --> 00:31:24,160
you never know when it'll come,

724
00:31:24,160 --> 00:31:25,240
and it's fleeting.

725
00:31:25,440 --> 00:31:27,240
So I have to grab hold of it tight.

726
00:31:31,880 --> 00:31:33,140
If I hadn't called you,

727
00:31:33,180 --> 00:31:34,810
you'd really have skipped breakfast?

728
00:31:34,810 --> 00:31:35,660
That won't do.

729
00:31:36,900 --> 00:31:38,070
You need to eat properly

730
00:31:38,070 --> 00:31:39,330
before going to class.

731
00:31:49,310 --> 00:31:51,290
Have you been coming back
at this time every day?

732
00:31:51,290 --> 00:31:52,020
Pretty much.

733
00:31:54,940 --> 00:31:55,540
All yours.

734
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:56,690
I'm full.

735
00:31:56,770 --> 00:31:58,200
You're eating that little?

736
00:31:58,200 --> 00:31:59,480
Have a few more.

737
00:31:59,810 --> 00:32:02,740
Play on a full stomach,
sing on an empty one—you know?

738
00:32:04,090 --> 00:32:06,220
I think I've heard that saying before.

739
00:32:09,400 --> 00:32:09,960
In the future,

740
00:32:09,960 --> 00:32:11,760
we can have breakfast together.

741
00:32:12,030 --> 00:32:12,820
Sure!

742
00:32:14,050 --> 00:32:14,780
Sounds good!

743
00:32:15,310 --> 00:32:16,090
Perfect—I can't eat that much

744
00:32:16,090 --> 00:32:17,270
in the morning anyway.

745
00:32:17,270 --> 00:32:17,900
If we eat together,

746
00:32:17,900 --> 00:32:18,830
you can help me finish it.

747
00:32:18,830 --> 00:32:19,370
Sure!

748
00:32:19,640 --> 00:32:21,070
T-Then let's set a time?

749
00:32:22,610 --> 00:32:23,330
Half past six?

750
00:32:23,330 --> 00:32:24,200
-Okay.
-Good.

751
00:32:25,250 --> 00:32:26,610
From now on,

752
00:32:26,660 --> 00:32:28,660
one steamer is enough for both of us.

753
00:32:28,900 --> 00:32:29,830
You need to eat more.

754
00:32:29,830 --> 00:32:31,090
You're still growing.

755
00:32:31,400 --> 00:32:33,290
Me? Still growing?

756
00:32:33,490 --> 00:32:34,330
Look how old I am.

757
00:32:34,330 --> 00:32:35,350
I'm done growing.

758
00:32:35,460 --> 00:32:37,460
One steamer is just right—no waste.

759
00:32:37,530 --> 00:32:37,920
Fine.

760
00:32:39,590 --> 00:32:40,070
See?

761
00:32:40,090 --> 00:32:41,420
You pop them in one bite.

762
00:32:41,660 --> 00:32:43,110
Yes, one bite.

763
00:32:43,140 --> 00:32:45,140
Still, I can't finish two steamers.

764
00:32:46,570 --> 00:32:48,300
Can you eat one in a single bite?

765
00:32:48,330 --> 00:32:49,660
I can only have two buns.

766
00:32:49,940 --> 00:32:52,470
Play on a full stomach
and sing on an empty one.

767
00:32:53,140 --> 00:32:54,800
Here, Miss, raise your glass!

768
00:32:55,140 --> 00:32:56,240
Come on, cheers!

769
00:32:56,310 --> 00:32:57,870
Come on! Raise your glass!

770
00:32:58,270 --> 00:32:58,720
Right.

771
00:32:59,030 --> 00:32:59,620
Clink!

772
00:33:04,010 --> 00:33:04,840
Good, good.

773
00:33:04,960 --> 00:33:06,510
Come on, let's have another one!

774
00:33:06,510 --> 00:33:07,380
Mr. Wang, Mr. Wang.

775
00:33:07,380 --> 00:33:08,030
Come on.

776
00:33:08,380 --> 00:33:10,070
Don't just focus on Ranran.

777
00:33:10,110 --> 00:33:11,570
Have one with me, will you?

778
00:33:12,220 --> 00:33:13,440
Let's have one together!

779
00:33:13,440 --> 00:33:14,790
You can't neglect me
for a pretty face, right?

780
00:33:14,790 --> 00:33:15,690
I'll drink with you!

781
00:33:15,690 --> 00:33:16,150
Cheers!

782
00:33:16,210 --> 00:33:16,670
Cheers!

783
00:33:17,510 --> 00:33:18,230
Thanks.

784
00:33:20,310 --> 00:33:20,920
Miss,

785
00:33:21,700 --> 00:33:23,160
raise your glass. Together!

786
00:33:23,160 --> 00:33:24,220
What's wrong?

787
00:33:24,510 --> 00:33:24,960
Come on.

788
00:33:24,960 --> 00:33:25,880
Bottoms up, bottoms up.

789
00:33:25,880 --> 00:33:26,830
-Mr. Wang.
-Look at you.

790
00:33:26,830 --> 00:33:27,360
Mr. Wang!

791
00:33:27,500 --> 00:33:28,230
Listen to me.

792
00:33:28,750 --> 00:33:29,610
Our Ranran here

793
00:33:29,980 --> 00:33:31,550
is an absolutely great actress.

794
00:33:31,550 --> 00:33:32,900
Last time, due to scheduling conflicts,

795
00:33:32,900 --> 00:33:34,500
she had to miss out on my show.

796
00:33:34,980 --> 00:33:35,750
Aren't you currently

797
00:33:35,750 --> 00:33:37,220
investing in a new production?

798
00:33:37,220 --> 00:33:37,900
I've looked into it.

799
00:33:37,900 --> 00:33:39,510
The production scale is decent.

800
00:33:39,510 --> 00:33:41,090
You shouldn't miss out on her again.

801
00:33:41,090 --> 00:33:43,080
We need to use a good actress like her!

802
00:33:43,080 --> 00:33:43,790
I'm telling you—

803
00:33:43,790 --> 00:33:45,640
I'm sharing a gem,
and it pains me to do so.

804
00:33:45,640 --> 00:33:46,770
If it weren't for our relationship,

805
00:33:46,770 --> 00:33:47,850
I wouldn't introduce her to you at all.

806
00:33:47,850 --> 00:33:48,780
You understand?

807
00:33:49,790 --> 00:33:51,010
I get it. I get it.

808
00:33:53,050 --> 00:33:53,880
Come on, miss.

809
00:33:54,720 --> 00:33:55,500
Have another cup.

810
00:33:55,500 --> 00:33:56,330
Mr. Wang, Mr. Wang,

811
00:33:56,330 --> 00:33:56,970
listen to me.

812
00:33:56,970 --> 00:33:58,100
I haven't finished.

813
00:33:59,010 --> 00:33:59,550
I'm telling you,

814
00:33:59,550 --> 00:34:00,460
young actors

815
00:34:00,480 --> 00:34:01,400
like her

816
00:34:01,590 --> 00:34:02,810
are just like grass.

817
00:34:03,440 --> 00:34:05,460
As long as people like us
give them more water

818
00:34:05,460 --> 00:34:06,520
and more sunlight,

819
00:34:07,240 --> 00:34:09,100
sooner or later, they will bloom.

820
00:34:11,550 --> 00:34:13,280
Mr. Chu, that metaphor of yours

821
00:34:13,360 --> 00:34:14,730
is really something.

822
00:34:15,030 --> 00:34:15,850
Sunshine.

823
00:34:16,570 --> 00:34:17,969
Grass.

824
00:34:19,170 --> 00:34:21,030
Let me take a look at this "grass."

825
00:34:21,480 --> 00:34:22,870
Take a look. Go ahead.

826
00:34:32,340 --> 00:34:34,000
This "grass" looks...

827
00:34:34,400 --> 00:34:35,130
pretty good.

828
00:34:36,190 --> 00:34:37,250
It's just...

829
00:34:37,590 --> 00:34:39,150
I wonder how her acting is.

830
00:34:39,210 --> 00:34:39,810
Good!

831
00:34:39,980 --> 00:34:41,040
Her acting is good.

832
00:34:41,130 --> 00:34:41,989
How do you know?

833
00:34:42,000 --> 00:34:43,280
There isn't even a script.

834
00:34:43,280 --> 00:34:44,420
Well, how about this?

835
00:34:44,420 --> 00:34:47,090
How about letting her show us a talent?

836
00:34:48,460 --> 00:34:49,190
Show us a talent?

837
00:34:49,190 --> 00:34:50,389
You... Aren't you...

838
00:34:50,420 --> 00:34:51,190
Well, Wang,

839
00:34:51,360 --> 00:34:51,820
you...

840
00:34:51,960 --> 00:34:53,320
Is that really necessary?

841
00:34:53,320 --> 00:34:54,710
Don't you trust my judgment?

842
00:34:54,710 --> 00:34:55,889
Trust me on this.

843
00:34:56,840 --> 00:34:58,370
I've got things to do today.

844
00:34:58,500 --> 00:34:59,560
Let's call it a day.

845
00:35:00,550 --> 00:35:01,410
Check, please!

846
00:35:01,530 --> 00:35:02,170
Waiter!

847
00:35:02,320 --> 00:35:03,430
Over here! Waiter!

848
00:35:05,970 --> 00:35:06,790
I can dance.

849
00:35:08,860 --> 00:35:09,600
I can dance.

850
00:35:10,730 --> 00:35:11,170
Good.

851
00:35:12,070 --> 00:35:13,470
If you want to be a star,

852
00:35:13,670 --> 00:35:15,330
you've got to have that drive!

853
00:35:15,880 --> 00:35:16,510
Yes, yes.

854
00:35:23,920 --> 00:35:24,940
Good! Good!

855
00:36:17,070 --> 00:36:17,920
Bravo! Bravo!

856
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:18,860
Bravo! Bravo!

857
00:36:18,960 --> 00:36:20,630
Now that's a one-in-a-million talent!

858
00:36:20,630 --> 00:36:21,920
A talent. I told you!

859
00:36:28,210 --> 00:36:28,940
Let's drink.

860
00:36:29,190 --> 00:36:29,760
Cheers.

861
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:42,100
Where is she?

862
00:36:42,420 --> 00:36:43,350
Why has she gone?

863
00:36:46,950 --> 00:36:49,220
She's just so cute.

864
00:37:22,090 --> 00:37:23,950
Come on, I'll walk you to the door.

865
00:37:25,590 --> 00:37:27,420
Mrs. Zheng, I'm leaving now.

866
00:37:27,510 --> 00:37:28,440
Leaving so soon?

867
00:37:28,570 --> 00:37:29,530
Then I won't see you out.

868
00:37:29,530 --> 00:37:30,260
That's fine.

869
00:37:30,920 --> 00:37:31,980
You must remember.

870
00:37:32,570 --> 00:37:34,420
Take good care of your voice.

871
00:37:34,510 --> 00:37:34,980
Mr. Zheng.

872
00:37:34,980 --> 00:37:35,420
If...

873
00:37:36,110 --> 00:37:36,530
What is this?

874
00:37:36,530 --> 00:37:38,090
Thank you for your help last time.

875
00:37:38,090 --> 00:37:39,980
I told you, there's no hurry.

876
00:37:40,010 --> 00:37:43,210
-I must pay you back.
-The meal is ready. Zhuang Zhuang...

877
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:49,070
What's this about?

878
00:37:49,400 --> 00:37:50,330
Explain it to me.

879
00:37:51,260 --> 00:37:53,660
It's Zhuang Zhuang's... tuition.

880
00:37:53,710 --> 00:37:55,170
Didn't she already pay it?

881
00:37:56,380 --> 00:37:57,900
I paid for her.

882
00:37:58,070 --> 00:38:00,070
Well, aren't you something, Zheng.

883
00:38:00,210 --> 00:38:01,440
You teach her

884
00:38:01,480 --> 00:38:03,610
and cover her tuition on top of it, huh?

885
00:38:04,460 --> 00:38:05,500
What are you after?

886
00:38:05,500 --> 00:38:06,900
I told you already.

887
00:38:07,000 --> 00:38:09,260
When Zhuang Zhuang first came to Beijing,

888
00:38:09,260 --> 00:38:10,800
her wallet was stolen.

889
00:38:10,900 --> 00:38:12,500
She didn't have money for tuition,

890
00:38:12,500 --> 00:38:14,380
so she had to work part-time to
earn money.

891
00:38:14,380 --> 00:38:15,170
Because she didn't have the money,

892
00:38:15,170 --> 00:38:16,550
you paid out of your own pocket?

893
00:38:16,550 --> 00:38:17,570
Well, if I didn't,

894
00:38:17,690 --> 00:38:18,150
what...

895
00:38:19,050 --> 00:38:19,630
what would she do?

896
00:38:19,630 --> 00:38:21,030
You could have told me!

897
00:38:21,090 --> 00:38:22,340
Like I have the guts.

898
00:38:22,650 --> 00:38:23,580
You didn't dare?

899
00:38:23,610 --> 00:38:24,230
Am I really

900
00:38:24,260 --> 00:38:25,660
an unreasonable person?

901
00:38:26,940 --> 00:38:28,380
Come clean right now.

902
00:38:28,570 --> 00:38:29,960
You've been keeping a secret stash.

903
00:38:29,960 --> 00:38:31,650
Since when?

904
00:38:31,840 --> 00:38:32,670
And how much is left?

905
00:38:32,670 --> 00:38:33,690
Where have you been hiding it?

906
00:38:33,690 --> 00:38:35,530
You're telling me everything today!

907
00:38:35,530 --> 00:38:37,650
Are you trying to blow up this marriage?

908
00:38:37,650 --> 00:38:38,920
Watch your words.

909
00:38:38,940 --> 00:38:40,210
-Watch what?
-Why do you have to say it so nastily?

910
00:38:40,210 --> 00:38:41,090
How is it nasty?

911
00:38:41,190 --> 00:38:42,150
My words are nasty?

912
00:38:42,150 --> 00:38:43,860
Isn't what you did nasty?

913
00:38:44,030 --> 00:38:45,530
You have to admit it!

914
00:38:45,940 --> 00:38:47,430
Zheng, I'm telling you—

915
00:38:47,480 --> 00:38:48,880
whatever else you're hiding from me,

916
00:38:48,880 --> 00:38:50,650
you'd better come clean today!

917
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:52,760
Otherwise, there'll be hell to pay!

918
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:55,590
Zongbao,

919
00:38:56,110 --> 00:38:57,210
tell me...

920
00:38:58,920 --> 00:39:00,400
Where could Cao have gone?

921
00:39:01,260 --> 00:39:02,880
How's he doing now?

922
00:39:06,550 --> 00:39:08,110
Let's think positively.

923
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:10,420
Cao...

924
00:39:12,610 --> 00:39:13,810
has gone to Xinjiang.

925
00:39:14,380 --> 00:39:15,670
To gather inspiration

926
00:39:15,800 --> 00:39:16,880
and paint.

927
00:39:17,260 --> 00:39:19,300
To see the snow-capped mountains

928
00:39:19,630 --> 00:39:21,090
and the grasslands there.

929
00:39:21,230 --> 00:39:22,150
Maybe,

930
00:39:22,230 --> 00:39:23,940
in Dabancheng,

931
00:39:24,500 --> 00:39:25,430
he'll meet a girl

932
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,980
and fall head over heels.

933
00:39:28,690 --> 00:39:29,510
Next year,

934
00:39:29,820 --> 00:39:31,750
he'll come back to our room, right?

935
00:39:32,090 --> 00:39:33,210
With a kid along.

936
00:39:35,300 --> 00:39:35,960
I hope so.

937
00:39:37,290 --> 00:39:38,430
Best wishes to him.

938
00:39:38,980 --> 00:39:40,180
Xu, what do you think?

939
00:39:44,550 --> 00:39:45,800
Xu, why are you so quiet?

940
00:39:45,800 --> 00:39:47,730
Thinking about the one in Room 116?

941
00:39:47,840 --> 00:39:49,690
No, I'm pondering a scene.

942
00:39:49,860 --> 00:39:50,660
What scene?

943
00:39:50,940 --> 00:39:51,740
What scene?

944
00:39:53,030 --> 00:39:55,170
Mr. He described a scene.

945
00:39:56,070 --> 00:39:57,170
It was really good.

946
00:39:57,550 --> 00:39:57,920
See?

947
00:39:58,610 --> 00:39:59,690
He's got serious work.

948
00:39:59,690 --> 00:40:01,260
Yeah, he described it well.

949
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:02,810
Why did you pull a long face?

950
00:40:03,050 --> 00:40:04,230
But I just feel...

951
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:06,590
there's a better way to handle it.

952
00:40:06,590 --> 00:40:07,570
Then tell him

953
00:40:07,590 --> 00:40:08,400
your ideas.

954
00:40:10,170 --> 00:40:11,630
That... That won't do.

955
00:40:12,170 --> 00:40:13,880
We call him the great screenwriter,

956
00:40:13,880 --> 00:40:16,980
but that title only counts

957
00:40:16,980 --> 00:40:17,920
within these four walls.

958
00:40:17,920 --> 00:40:19,180
When you're out there,

959
00:40:19,230 --> 00:40:21,000
you have to keep your head down,

960
00:40:21,010 --> 00:40:21,510
am I right?

961
00:40:21,510 --> 00:40:24,010
You can't go around
giving your mentor advice.

962
00:40:24,010 --> 00:40:24,870
Remember that.

963
00:40:26,880 --> 00:40:27,960
Little Northeasterner

964
00:40:27,960 --> 00:40:29,090
told me the other day

965
00:40:29,170 --> 00:40:30,230
that when Cao left,

966
00:40:30,280 --> 00:40:31,480
he still owed rent.

967
00:40:32,360 --> 00:40:33,190
And on top of that,

968
00:40:33,190 --> 00:40:34,650
Cao owed him some cab fare.

969
00:40:35,230 --> 00:40:36,210
We've all lived together

970
00:40:36,210 --> 00:40:37,150
for so long.

971
00:40:37,190 --> 00:40:38,510
We have a bond.

972
00:40:39,210 --> 00:40:41,330
We can't let Cao's name

973
00:40:41,460 --> 00:40:43,060
get tarnished in the hostel.

974
00:40:43,820 --> 00:40:44,860
I say we do this—

975
00:40:45,280 --> 00:40:47,030
the three of us chip in some money

976
00:40:47,030 --> 00:40:47,760
and pay off

977
00:40:47,860 --> 00:40:48,420
his debt.

978
00:40:48,960 --> 00:40:49,960
What do you think?

979
00:40:50,090 --> 00:40:51,280
We pay?

980
00:40:52,420 --> 00:40:53,880
You tell Northeasterner—

981
00:40:53,980 --> 00:40:55,690
a small loss can lead to a bigger gain.

982
00:40:55,690 --> 00:40:56,150
Well...

983
00:40:56,530 --> 00:40:57,730
Zongbao,

984
00:40:58,070 --> 00:40:59,600
we've been living together

985
00:40:59,610 --> 00:41:00,780
for so long.

986
00:41:01,010 --> 00:41:03,270
Why is it that when money comes up, you...

987
00:41:05,860 --> 00:41:07,120
That man here is right.

988
00:41:07,260 --> 00:41:09,320
A small loss can lead to a bigger gain.

989
00:41:09,400 --> 00:41:10,060
Who are you?

990
00:41:11,590 --> 00:41:12,380
I'm telling you,

991
00:41:12,380 --> 00:41:14,320
a small loss really can
lead to a bigger gain.

992
00:41:14,320 --> 00:41:15,920
Sometimes when you take a loss,

993
00:41:15,920 --> 00:41:17,500
the other person remembers your kindness.

994
00:41:17,500 --> 00:41:18,590
Who knows—one day,

995
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:20,090
they might repay your small kindness

996
00:41:20,090 --> 00:41:20,960
a hundredfold!

997
00:41:21,210 --> 00:41:21,880
By then...

998
00:41:22,730 --> 00:41:24,000
you'll come out way ahead,

999
00:41:24,000 --> 00:41:24,460
right?

1000
00:41:24,510 --> 00:41:25,260
Well, why are you here?

1001
00:41:25,260 --> 00:41:25,920
Who is this?

1002
00:41:27,340 --> 00:41:28,500
You sure make yourself at home
with strangers.

1003
00:41:28,500 --> 00:41:30,230
Well, it just kind of happened.

1004
00:41:30,630 --> 00:41:31,230
Everyone,

1005
00:41:32,750 --> 00:41:34,080
Comrade Cao Ye has gone.

1006
00:41:34,550 --> 00:41:35,690
Just like that—he left us

1007
00:41:35,690 --> 00:41:36,380
quietly.

1008
00:41:36,510 --> 00:41:38,260
Are you delivering a eulogy or what?

1009
00:41:38,260 --> 00:41:39,460
Who is this?

1010
00:41:40,960 --> 00:41:41,760
Cao Ye left,

1011
00:41:42,380 --> 00:41:43,980
but his bed can't stay empty.

1012
00:41:44,360 --> 00:41:45,010
Around here,

1013
00:41:45,010 --> 00:41:46,420
every spot has to be filled.

1014
00:41:46,420 --> 00:41:48,150
From now on, this gentleman here

1015
00:41:48,150 --> 00:41:49,160
is joining us.

1016
00:41:49,530 --> 00:41:50,050
His name is...

1017
00:41:50,050 --> 00:41:50,510
Xiaobo.

1018
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:53,030
I'm Li Xiaobo!

1019
00:41:55,050 --> 00:41:55,690
Everyone,

1020
00:41:55,780 --> 00:41:57,420
let's get close from now on.

1021
00:41:57,730 --> 00:41:58,840
Let's look out for each other.

1022
00:41:58,840 --> 00:41:59,780
Come on, make way.

1023
00:41:59,780 --> 00:42:01,090
Let's get close!

1024
00:42:01,940 --> 00:42:03,320
Let's share the blessings.

1025
00:42:03,320 --> 00:42:04,300
Come on, come on.

1026
00:42:04,650 --> 00:42:05,630
Let's share the blessings.

1027
00:42:05,630 --> 00:42:06,370
No, no, no.

1028
00:42:06,630 --> 00:42:07,090
I get it.

1029
00:42:07,670 --> 00:42:08,780
And share the hardships too.

1030
00:42:08,780 --> 00:42:09,610
Here, take this.

1031
00:42:09,610 --> 00:42:10,500
No, no, no.

1032
00:42:10,590 --> 00:42:11,920
That's not what I meant.

1033
00:42:12,230 --> 00:42:13,690
And share the hardships too.

1034
00:42:13,690 --> 00:42:15,530
Let's share the blessings
and the hardships.

1035
00:42:15,530 --> 00:42:16,550
As for me,

1036
00:42:17,340 --> 00:42:18,920
I go to bed early and get up early.

1037
00:42:18,920 --> 00:42:20,120
If I ever disturb you,

1038
00:42:20,880 --> 00:42:22,010
please bear with me!

1039
00:42:22,460 --> 00:42:23,590
Please bear with me.

1040
00:42:25,170 --> 00:42:26,230
It's getting late.

1041
00:42:26,300 --> 00:42:26,760
Give me.

1042
00:42:29,880 --> 00:42:30,680
Time to sleep!

1043
00:42:37,360 --> 00:42:37,960
Go to sleep.

1044
00:42:37,960 --> 00:42:38,420
Come on.

1045
00:42:38,730 --> 00:42:39,190
Come on.

1046
00:42:39,630 --> 00:42:40,830
I need to make the bed.

1047
00:42:42,460 --> 00:42:42,990
Alright.

1048
00:42:43,610 --> 00:42:44,410
Time to sleep!

1049
00:42:49,210 --> 00:42:49,810
It's okay.

1050
00:42:50,170 --> 00:42:51,430
You guys keep talking.

1051
00:42:51,900 --> 00:42:52,900
I had a long day today.
